The National Working Committee of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), has appointed the former Kaduna State Governor, Senator Ahmed Makarfi as Chairman Anambra Local Government Area Congresses Appeal Committee. PDP National Publicity Secretary, Hon. Debo Ologunagba, on Monday, said the committee is to consider appeals arising from the conduct of the Local Government Area Congresses in Anambra State. The party also appointed Amb. Sen. Umar El-Gash as secretary. Other members of the committee are; Dame Dr Esther Uduehi, Chief Danladi Sunday, Barr. Paul Abu, Mr Mike Ahumibe and Hajiya Fatima Saleh. According to the statement, the exercise is scheduled to hold on Tuesday, March 01, 2022, at the PDP National Secretariat, Wadata Plaza, Wuse Zone 5, Abuja.